                new FreePaintTextureLoader.FreePaintTextureParameter(
                    new FreePaintTextureLoader.Painter() {
                        @Override
                        public void draw(final Gdx2DPixmap pixmap) {
                            pixmap.fillRect(...);
                            // utility method of FreePaintTextureLoader.Painter
                            applyNoise(pixmap);
                            pixmap.fillCircle(...);
                            // anything else
                        }
                    },
                    Gdx.graphics.getWidth(), 
                    Gdx.graphics.getHeight()),
                FreePaintTexture.class
        )
);
```

Code smells are defined as symptom s in the program source code which are usually not bugs or technically incorrect but indicates a possible deeper problem. Anti-patterns are counterparts of design patterns and are defined as mistakes during software development that produces negative consequences and is ineffective or counter-productive. During program execution, error events can occur that disrupts the normal flow of the program. Programming languages provide exception handling mechanism to developers for handling errors and exception events. 

I mined the source-code for automatically detecting 10 exception handling anti-patterns (https://today.java.net/article/2006/04/04/exception-handling-antipatterns).  In this issue report, I list the exception handling anti-patterns and code-smells that I found in the source code. My experimental results demonstrate presence of various exception handling anti-patterns and throw light on their intensity. I believe my tool for automatic detection of anti-patterns in source code and the attached 

1 Mining Source Code for Automatically Discovering Exception Management Anti-Patterns and Code Smell

